HOUSE JOINT RESOLUTION 121
By Maberry
A RESOLUTION to honor the memory of Sarah Lee Best.
WHEREAS, it was with great sadness that the members of this General Assembly
learned of the untimely death of Sarah Lee Best; and
WHEREAS, a native of Clarksville, Ms. Best was an attorney with Wilkinson Stekloff Law
Firm in Washington, D.C.; and
WHEREAS, a gifted and dedicated student, Sarah Best graduated summa cum laude
with a Bachelor of Arts degree in Neuroscience and Classical Languages from Vanderbilt
University in 2013; and
WHEREAS, she then taught high school math and worked as an instructional coach in
her native Tennessee before entering law school; and
WHEREAS, Ms. Best graduated summa cum laude from the University of Pennsylvania
Law School, where her former professors praise her as a brilliant student and a beloved
member of the school's community; and
WHEREAS, during her tenure in law school, Sarah Best was a senior editor of the
University of Pennsylvania Law Review, served on the board of Penn's Asian Pacific American
Law Student Association, interned for the U.S. Department of Education's Office of the General
Counsel, completed an externship with the Education Law Center, and worked in the
Transnational Legal Clinic, where she represented clients seeking asylum; and
WHEREAS, she also was inducted into the Order of the Coif, received the David Werner
Amram Prize and the Exceptional Pro Bono Service Award, and was named the Edwin R.
Keedy Cup Moot Court Winner and Best Oralist; and
